  "market_context": "Price in established uptrend with prior bullish breaks of structure; unmitigated order block at lower extreme, dynamic liquidity below upward-sloping trendline. Price pulled back to mitigate the OB and sweep liquidity before reversal.",
  "key_observation": "After sweeping sell-side liquidity below the trendline, price formed a three-candle sequence culminating in a bullish engulfing candle that broke above the mitigated order block, confirming long entry.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: Identified an unmitigated order block at the lower extreme and dynamic liquidity below the bullish trendline on the 1H EURUSD chart.",
    "Step 2: Anticipated price would push lower to mitigate the order block and sweep the liquidity below the trendline.",
    "Step 3: Observed price sweeping liquidity and reaching the key OB zone, forming a three-candle pattern: first candle mitigated the OB, second showed rejection, third was a bullish engulfing candle breaking above the OB and engulfing the reaction candle.",
    "Step 4: Entered long at close of engulfing candle, placed stop loss below the low of the reaction candle, and set take profit at buyside liquidity above the recent swing high."
  ],
  "outcome": "Take-profit level was successfully hit as price rallied with strong momentum above the swing high after entry.",
  "lessons": "A valid long setup requires: (1) context of uptrend with BOS, (2) liquidity sweep below trendline, (3) mitigation of unmitigated OB, and (4) confirmation via engulfing candle—entry only after full pattern completion.",
